  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Kayin Flood response 2019</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">From this activity 9,131 women and girls and  5,871 men and boys will access basic food items and hygiene kits which is in urgent need. This will also prevent them from malnutrition and skin diseases. This assistance will enable the communities to plan for the future livelihoods and rehabilitation without any concerns on the urgent need of food and hygiene care.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">KBC will distribute basic food items and hygiene kits to 3000 households reaching to 15000 population in 28 villages under Kawkareik and Kyar In Seik Townships in Kayin State. Hygiene kits would include tooth paste, tooth brush, Soaps, Sanitary pads, Bucket with lid, soap box and water purification tablets/drops. Food ration kits would include Rice, vegetable cooking oil, salt and beans/lentils for the basic food needs for one month. During the distribution of these items, hygiene campaigns will be carried out at the same time. Monitoring and accountability systems will be set up to ensure the beneficiaries receive assistance as intended. Coordination with other agencies and stakeholders will be carried out to avoid overlap and better collaboration and assistance to the affected communities.</narrative>
  </description>
